headline: U.S. Small Business Employment Growth Remains Consistent as Weekly Hours Worked Reach Near-Decade High
summary: ROCHESTER, N.Y., November 04, 2025--According to the latest Paychex Small Business Employment Watch, which is based on the payroll data of Paychex’s customers with fewer than 50 employees, small business employment levels remained consistent in October. The report’s Small Business Jobs Index has moved less than one percentage point over the last year, indicating continued moderation in small business hiring. thumbnail.caption: Hourly earnings growth for workers in U.S. businesses with fewer than 50 employees remained below three percent for the 15th consecutive month in October, according to the Paychex Small Business Employment Watch.
